{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The request sent to the external API always includes the complete list of valid taxonomy labels.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is the module-to-client handoff: taxonomy must survive request construction and serialization into the outbound API payload. A pure Unit test of a helper can miss wiring/field-mapping defects. Rejected System because behavior text is about payload content (\"includes the complete list\"), not real network/OS effects. Rejected Agentic/Workflow because correctness does not depend on model judgment or multi-step agent decisions.","test_description":"Wire classifier + real request-construction path with a fake in-process API transport that captures outbound payload; assert every configured taxonomy label is present in the sent request for representative taxonomies.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When the API returns a label that is not in the taxonomy, the module returns \"unknown\" instead of forwarding the unexpected value to the caller.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is response-handling across API adapter + normalization/validation boundary. Minimal real-failure test should exercise parsing plus taxonomy guard together. Rejected Agentic because behavior is explicitly about a specific invalid returned value (\"returns a label that is not in the taxonomy\"), which can be deterministically injected by a stub. Rejected System because no real OS/network behavior is required.","test_description":"Run classifier with an in-process stub API returning out-of-taxonomy labels (case/whitespace variants too if supported); assert caller receives exactly \"unknown\" and never raw unexpected labels.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"For identical raw API responses, the module's normalization step always produces the same final label.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Behavior is a local determinism property of normalization logic given identical inputs; no module boundary or I/O is needed to expose real failure. Rejected higher levels because text scopes to \"normalization step\" with fixed raw responses.","test_description":"Directly test normalization function/object with repeated identical raw response fixtures and assert stable identical normalized label each run.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.9,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"On repeated live API calls for the same document and taxonomy, the returned label remains consistent unless the provider response itself changes.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Behavior explicitly requires \"repeated live API calls\" and label consistency tied to provider outputs, so it depends on real AI API behavior/non-determinism. Mocks would hide drift/variance failures. Rejected Workflow because this is repeated single-step classification, not a multi-stage agent pipeline with chained model decisions.","test_description":"Execute repeated real-provider classifications for fixed document+taxonomy under controlled prompt/model settings; record raw provider outputs and final labels, asserting label stability when raw provider response is unchanged, and allowing change only when provider response changes.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.03,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.85,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Request construction enforces the configured token budget before dispatch (for example truncate/reject according to policy).","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real failure is often at boundary between budget logic and dispatch path (e.g., policy computed but not enforced before send). Need modules wired together to verify \"before dispatch\". Rejected System because behavior text is pre-dispatch enforcement, not real network/OS effects. Rejected Agentic because model output quality is irrelevant.","test_description":"Run classifier through full pre-dispatch path with over-budget documents and in-process API stub; assert truncate/reject policy is applied and outbound request (if any) conforms to configured token budget before send.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Provider-reported token usage for a typical document stays within the configured per-call budget.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"This requires a real AI provider call and relies on provider-reported token accounting, which stubs cannot validate. Per rule, tests that pass through real AI/ML API calls default to Agentic unless purely infrastructure-only; here assertion is about provider usage semantics, not just transport. Rejected Workflow because only one model call step is evaluated.","test_description":"Issue real classification calls for representative typical documents and assert provider usage fields (prompt/total tokens as applicable) do not exceed configured per-call budget; fail on any budget breach.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.03,"System":0.25,"Agentic":0.7,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"When the API signals that the request rate is too high, the module waits and retries rather than returning an error to the caller.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Primary failure boundary is retry orchestration across API client + backoff policy + caller contract. Deterministic stubbed rate-limit responses can reproduce this class of failure. Rejected System because behavior text focuses on handling a signaled condition (\"API signals... waits and retries\"), which can be validated without real network. Rejected Agentic because no dependence on model output correctness.","test_description":"Use in-process stub API that returns rate-limit error then success; assert module delays/backs off per policy, retries, and returns successful label instead of surfacing initial rate-limit error.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}}]}
